01:24:02.454 --> 01:24:04.788
Yeah. but your mom is the
worst cook in the world.

1123
01:24:04.914 --> 01:24:07.750
Yo. don't you be talking about my momma.

1124
01:24:09.919 --> 01:24:12.421
Yeah. come on. baby. Who's good living?

1125
01:24:12.505 --> 01:24:14.631
To you. bro. Cheers. cheers. cheers.

1126
01:24:14.716 --> 01:24:16.967
ROME: So. we in Brazil.
It's the good life.

1127
01:24:17.052 --> 01:24:18.052
Yeah.

1128
01:24:18.136 --> 01:24:21.930
So. you got a little more
than $10 or $11 million coming.

1129
01:24:22.015 --> 01:24:23.140
What you going to do with your money?

1130
01:24:23.224 --> 01:24:24.892
Me? Yeah.

1131
01:24:24.976 --> 01:24:27.728
Actually. man. I been thinking
about opening up a garage back home.

1132
01:24:28.688 --> 01:24:31.482
Place where people can bring their
cars and not get completely ripped off.

1133
01:24:31.566 --> 01:24:32.691
You know what I mean?

1134
01:24:32.776 --> 01:24:34.109
Really? Yeah.

1135
01:24:34.194 --> 01:24:37.071
So. your dream is to start a day job?

1136
01:24:37.155 --> 01:24:39.323
That's stupid. Like. why would...

1137
01:24:39.407 --> 01:24:41.992
No. it's not stupid at
all. I love what I do.

1138
01:24:42.077 --> 01:24:43.077
That don't make no sense to me.

1139
01:24:43.161 --> 01:24:45.996
I know what I'm going
to do with my money.

1140
01:24:47.999 --> 01:24:49.917
Buying some cooking lessons for my man.

1141
01:24:50.418 --> 01:24:51.877
See? See?

1142
01:24:51.961 --> 01:24:54.254
There you go with that negativity. man.

1143
01:24:54.339 --> 01:24:56.381
You know me. Money
ain't a goddamn thing.

1144
01:24:56.466 --> 01:24:59.009
It's going to take a little more
than money to learn how to cook.

1145
01:24:59.094 --> 01:25:00.344
That's horrible.

1146
01:25:00.887 --> 01:25:04.556
But I heard they was looking for
a chef down at this animal shelter.

1147
01:25:04.641 --> 01:25:05.724
You might want to...

1148
01:25:05.809 --> 01:25:07.518
I know the manager.

1149
01:25:12.941 --> 01:25:14.608
Hey. Dom.

1150
01:25:17.320 --> 01:25:18.821
Listen.

1151
01:25:19.572 --> 01:25:23.283
I know that you're all
set for this job tomorrow.

1152
01:25:23.368 --> 01:25:25.119
but if you need an extra man. I could...

1153
01:25:25.203 --> 01:25:26.537
You're in.

1154
01:25:34.963 --> 01:25:36.505
There's always room for family.

1155
01:25:42.971 --> 01:25:44.012
Thank you.

1156
01:25:48.601 --> 01:25:49.726
Get something to eat.

1157
01:25:51.521 --> 01:25:53.147
Yeah.

1158
01:25:55.024 --> 01:25:56.733
Can you believe Mia calls this a curse?

1159
01:26:00.530 --> 01:26:02.698
She might be right.

1160
01:26:07.036 --> 01:26:09.496
You really like doing that stuff. huh?

1161
01:26:09.747 --> 01:26:14.001
When your life is on the line
that's when you learn about yourself.

1162
01:26:18.965 --> 01:26:20.716
That's a fair deal.

1163
01:26:24.012 --> 01:26:28.140
We're less than 24 hours from the
biggest celebration of our life.

1164
01:26:28.224 --> 01:26:30.517
Y'all need a refill.
This is serious stuff.

1165
01:26:30.602 --> 01:26:31.894
No. I'm good. Cheers. baby.

1166
01:26:31.978 --> 01:26:33.604
I'm good. No. thank you.

1167
01:26:33.688 --> 01:26:34.688
No. she can't.

1168
01:26:36.941 --> 01:26:38.942
What do you mean? She can't.

1169
01:26:39.277 --> 01:26:41.945
What do you mean she can't? What is...

1170
01:26:46.117 --> 01:26:48.368
Are you serious right now? (LAUGHING)

1171
01:26:48.453 --> 01:26:52.164
Is that the reason you let him
beat you in the quarter-mile?

1172
01:26:53.499 --> 01:26:56.752
That was a baby gift.
No. that's messed up.

1173
01:26:56.836 --> 01:26:58.420
No. you're not taking that from me.

1174
01:26:58.504 --> 01:27:00.130
Wait. wait. hold on a second.

1175
01:27:00.215 --> 01:27:04.509
So. did he just smack the ass
or did he grab and hold on to it?

1176
01:27:04.886 --> 01:27:05.886
Which one was it?

1177
01:27:05.970 --> 01:27:08.472
Congratulations. Thank you.

1178
01:27:08.598 --> 01:27:10.390
ROME: How can you keep this a secret?

1179
01:27:10.475 --> 01:27:12.476
Crazy. huh? ROME: It's your boy.

1180
01:27:12.602 --> 01:27:16.146
ROME: Why would you keep
something like that away from me?

1181
01:27:16.481 --> 01:27:18.273
Baby gift. huh?

1182
01:27:18.524 --> 01:27:21.360
I have no idea what
they're talking about. Oh?

1183
01:27:21.444 --> 01:27:24.446
TEJ: What happened to
the pull-out method. man?

1184
01:27:25.531 --> 01:27:27.574
Toast. Toast.

1185
01:27:35.917 --> 01:27:39.169
Money will come and go. We know that.

1186
01:27:40.296 --> 01:27:43.674
But the most important thing in life
will always be the people in this room.

1187
01:27:45.093 --> 01:27:46.343
Right here.

1188
01:27:48.972 --> 01:27:50.013
Right now.

1189
01:27:53.142 --> 01:27:54.142
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1190
01:27:55.186 --> 01:27:56.186
(ALL REPLYING IN ITALIAN)

1191
01:28:04.612 --> 01:28:06.196
I'm all set.

1192
01:28:07.198 --> 01:28:10.200
HAN: Yo. Santos. Van good?

1193
01:28:11.286 --> 01:28:13.495
You know we're always good. bro.

1194
01:28:17.375 --> 01:28:20.127
Hobbs is on the other side of the city.

1195
01:28:20.211 --> 01:28:22.796
We're not going to get a better window.

1196
01:28:22.880 --> 01:28:25.132
Okay. guys. it's show time!

1197
01:28:25.216 --> 01:28:26.800
First team in position. let's go.

1198
01:28:26.884 --> 01:28:28.135
TEGO: Come on. let's do this.

1199
01:28:40.440 --> 01:28:41.440
Hey. Dom.

1200
01:28:43.276 --> 01:28:44.401
I got eyes on Mia.

1201
01:28:49.407 --> 01:28:52.492
Moscow. Bali. Goa. Hong Kong.

1202
01:28:53.119 --> 01:28:54.995
And what do they all have in common?

1203
01:28:55.079 --> 01:28:56.163
No extradition.

1204
01:28:58.249 --> 01:29:01.001
We're one hour away from
the rest of our lives.

1205
01:29:01.085 --> 01:29:02.377
Yeah.

1206
01:29:04.088 --> 01:29:05.088
Cops!

1207
01:29:07.675 --> 01:29:09.051
Come on. Go.

1208
01:29:20.646 --> 01:29:22.272
You just made a big mistake.

1209
01:29:23.775 --> 01:29:25.692
Took me a while to
find that tracking chip.

1210
01:29:26.194 --> 01:29:27.569
But not as long to flip the receiver.

1211
01:29:27.653 --> 01:29:29.154
You're going down. Toretto.

1212
01:29:29.489 --> 01:29:31.281
I'm right here.

1213
01:29:31.491 --> 01:29:32.491
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1214
01:30:46.190 --> 01:30:47.190
(YELLING)

1215
01:30:59.412 --> 01:31:01.413
Dom! Stand back. I got this.

1216
01:31:07.336 --> 01:31:11.256
Pull off! Dom! Please. stop!

1217
01:31:16.888 --> 01:31:17.888
Dom!

1218
01:31:27.064 --> 01:31:28.398
Dom! (DOM SCREAMING)

1219
01:32:28.960 --> 01:32:29.960
(WALKIE TALKIE BEEPING)

1220
01:32:30.920 --> 01:32:31.962
Yeah.

1221
01:32:33.339 --> 01:32:35.298
We're coming in now.

1222
01:32:36.884 --> 01:32:39.553
Have the marshals meet us
at the airport when we land.

1223
01:32:47.436 --> 01:32:48.812
Ambush!

1224
01:33:06.455 --> 01:33:09.666
Wilkes. suppression
fire. Shut them down.

1225
01:33:13.879 --> 01:33:15.547
Stagger-step. Cover me.

1226
01:33:20.553 --> 01:33:21.595
Watch them!

1227
01:33:33.190 --> 01:33:34.274
Cut us loose!

1228
01:33:34.358 --> 01:33:36.359
Come on! Cut us loose!

1229
01:35:34.812 --> 01:35:36.187
We're good? Yeah. let's go. let's go!

1230
01:35:46.824 --> 01:35:47.824
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1231
01:35:58.294 --> 01:35:59.294
(SPITTING)

1232
01:36:09.472 --> 01:36:11.097
VINCE: Hey. Dom.

1233
01:36:17.354 --> 01:36:19.522
You've got to meet my son.

1234
01:36:19.815 --> 01:36:21.566
Nico.

1235
01:36:26.322 --> 01:36:27.781
I will.

1236
01:36:30.701 --> 01:36:31.951
He's a good kid.

1237
01:36:35.790 --> 01:36:38.416
You know. we named him after you.

1238
01:36:40.211 --> 01:36:41.544
"Dominic."

1239
01:36:48.803 --> 01:36:50.804
You've got my word. Vince.

1240
01:36:57.353 --> 01:36:59.437
You were always my brother.

1241
01:37:09.073 --> 01:37:11.574
I got eyes on Nico now.

1242
01:37:22.253 --> 01:37:24.671
We need to move. We
don't have that much time.

1243
01:37:24.755 --> 01:37:25.880
I got us a flight out.

1244
01:37:25.965 --> 01:37:28.550
We can leave Rio in the
rearview in the next five hours.

1245
01:37:28.634 --> 01:37:30.426
Not to run away.

1246
01:37:31.846 --> 01:37:33.429
To finish the job.

1247
01:37:34.265 --> 01:37:36.683
Are you crazy. Dom? We can't.

1248
01:37:37.268 --> 01:37:38.852
ROME: It's a suicide mission.

1249
01:37:39.937 --> 01:37:41.604
That's your man over there on the table.

1250
01:37:42.982 --> 01:37:45.024
The plan is busted!

1251
01:37:45.317 --> 01:37:47.819
This is bullshit. man.
Reyes knows we're coming!

1252
01:37:47.903 --> 01:37:49.279
TEJ: He's right.

1253
01:37:49.572 --> 01:37:52.365
They tripled the detail
at the police station.

1254
01:37:52.783 --> 01:37:55.034
TEJ: It's going to be a wall of gunfire.

1255
01:37:57.246 --> 01:37:59.330
Reyes doesn't get away with this.

1256
01:37:59.623 --> 01:38:00.623
It's a trap. man.

1257
01:38:00.708 --> 01:38:02.125
You know that.

1258
01:38:02.793 --> 01:38:05.128
Dom. listen to them.

1259
01:38:05.796 --> 01:38:08.381
Run. before it's too late. Leave Rio.

1260
01:38:09.758 --> 01:38:11.092
You can be free.

1261
01:38:13.262 --> 01:38:15.263
Running ain't freedom.

1262
01:38:16.724 --> 01:38:18.141
You should know that.

1263
01:38:23.230 --> 01:38:25.648
You know you're all free
to make your own choices.

1264
01:38:29.862 --> 01:38:30.987
HOBBS: I'm in.

1265
01:38:40.372 --> 01:38:41.998
I'll ride with you. Toretto.

1266
01:38:45.294 --> 01:38:47.837
At least until we kill
that son of a bitch.

1267
01:38:56.263 --> 01:38:57.847
BRIAN: So what's the plan. Dom?

1268
01:38:58.682 --> 01:39:00.725
We can't just go
sneaking around anymore.

1269
01:39:02.227 --> 01:39:04.187
We don't sneak.

1270
01:39:04.980 --> 01:39:08.107
The only thing he cares
about is his money.

1271
01:39:08.359 --> 01:39:09.692
We pull that.

1272
01:39:10.694 --> 01:39:12.111
we pull him.

1273
01:39:24.541 --> 01:39:25.583
(SECURITY DOOR BUZZING)

1274
01:39:28.379 --> 01:39:29.420
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

1275
01:39:29.505 --> 01:39:30.546
See?

1276
01:39:31.715 --> 01:39:34.384
I called in every cop on our payroll.

1277
01:39:35.886 --> 01:39:37.679
We're covered.

1278
01:39:39.390 --> 01:39:40.807
We've got every entrance
covered with weapons teams.

1279
01:39:40.891 --> 01:39:43.643
God Himself couldn't get at
your money if He wanted to.

1280
01:39:44.144 --> 01:39:48.481
God isn't my worry.

1281
01:39:58.242 --> 01:39:59.242
You ready?

1282
01:40:01.537 --> 01:40:02.537
I'm ready.

1283
01:40:40.075 --> 01:40:41.075
(POLICE OFFICERS CHATTERING)

1284
01:40:59.678 --> 01:41:00.803
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

1285
01:41:00.888 --> 01:41:02.013
What's happening?

1286
01:41:02.097 --> 01:41:03.556
They're taking the vault!

1287
01:41:03.640 --> 01:41:05.308
What? The vault!

1288
01:41:14.860 --> 01:41:18.112
Follow me! Quickly!

1289
01:41:22.451 --> 01:41:23.951
Let me through!

1290
01:41:34.004 --> 01:41:35.004
Don't move!

1291
01:41:36.215 --> 01:41:37.590
Stay down.

1292
01:42:07.579 --> 01:42:08.955
Call it out. Mia!

1293
01:42:09.039 --> 01:42:10.540
You've got a straight
shot for two blocks.

1294
01:42:12.042 --> 01:42:13.543
Go right. Got it.

1295
01:42:21.301 --> 01:42:22.301
(PEDESTRIANS SCREAMING)

1296
01:42:35.941 --> 01:42:37.525
Well. the plan is working.

1297
01:42:37.609 --> 01:42:42.488
You guys have every corrupt cop in Rio
on your tail. You have to move fast.

1298
01:42:42.573 --> 01:42:43.656
What's the best route?

1299
01:42:43.740 --> 01:42:46.993
Okay. keep going straight another
half-mile onto Rua Fonseca.

1300
01:42:47.077 --> 01:42:48.995
and then go left.

1301
01:42:52.749 --> 01:42:53.791
That ain't going to work.

1302
01:42:55.878 --> 01:42:57.461
Spikes ahead. Dom. We got spikes!

1303
01:42:57.880 --> 01:42:59.463
We're going right!

1304
01:43:00.841 --> 01:43:02.133
No. it's too tight.
we're not going to fit.

1305
01:43:02.217 --> 01:43:03.676
We've got no choice. Now!

1306
01:43:13.103 --> 01:43:14.103
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1307
01:43:23.363 --> 01:43:24.530
Shit!

1308
01:43:31.163 --> 01:43:32.455
Holy shit!

1309
01:43:32.539 --> 01:43:35.416
Guys. I am hearing all this chatter.
Did you just take out a bank?

1310
01:43:44.468 --> 01:43:45.468
Two inbound!

1311
01:43:47.888 --> 01:43:49.347
All right. there's an alley
coming up on your left.

1312
01:43:49.431 --> 01:43:51.098
Yeah. I got it.

1313
01:44:30.639 --> 01:44:31.639
(GUNSHOTS)

1314
01:44:37.688 --> 01:44:38.688
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1315
01:44:39.314 --> 01:44:40.314
(GRUNTING)

1316
01:44:44.486 --> 01:44:46.112
You little bastard!

1317
01:45:09.261 --> 01:45:11.971
All right. good job. Dom.
Right-hander. right here. right-hander.

1318
01:45:18.353 --> 01:45:20.396
Guys. there's a big group
coming at you from the south.

1319
01:45:20.480 --> 01:45:22.273
You have to do something now!

1320
01:45:25.152 --> 01:45:26.193
Hey. go wide.

1321
01:45:48.175 --> 01:45:49.175
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

1322
01:45:49.885 --> 01:45:50.885
(CHUCKLING)

1323
01:45:58.977 --> 01:45:59.977
Yeah!

1324
01:46:18.747 --> 01:46:19.747
(POLICE CAR HONKING)

1325
01:46:38.183 --> 01:46:39.183
(BULLETS HITTING CAR)

1326
01:47:04.334 --> 01:47:05.334
(GRUNTING)

1327
01:47:13.844 --> 01:47:15.136
You're all clear on the left.

1328
01:47:15.220 --> 01:47:17.054
Good afternoon. officer!

1329
01:47:19.057 --> 01:47:21.475
License and registration. please!

1330
01:47:27.691 --> 01:47:30.568
Yes! This is big-boy stuff!

1331
01:47:30.652 --> 01:47:32.069
We're clear on the right.

1332
01:47:32.320 --> 01:47:33.404
Oh. man.

1333
01:47:40.203 --> 01:47:41.245
Thanks. guys.

1334
01:47:41.621 --> 01:47:42.746
Any time.

1335
01:47:43.039 --> 01:47:44.623
I'll see you on the other side.

1336
01:47:44.708 --> 01:47:47.001
You guys just carved
out a 1 0-second window.

1337
01:47:47.085 --> 01:47:48.544
Make it count!

1338
01:47:54.718 --> 01:47:55.801
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

1339
01:47:55.886 --> 01:47:57.052
Zizi. stay on them.

1340
01:48:23.580 --> 01:48:25.498
They can't outrun us on the bridge.

1341
01:48:27.459 --> 01:48:28.459
Shit.

1342
01:48:35.550 --> 01:48:36.759
They have no way out.

1343
01:48:38.762 --> 01:48:39.762
No!

1344
01:48:40.597 --> 01:48:41.680
There's too many of them.

1345
01:48:41.765 --> 01:48:43.724
Hey. there's too many of them.
We're not going to make it.

1346
01:48:47.437 --> 01:48:48.437
You're right. we aren't.

1347
01:48:49.731 --> 01:48:50.689
You are.

1348
01:48:50.774 --> 01:48:52.066
What are you talking about?

1349
01:48:52.275 --> 01:48:54.693
Just let the vault go. Get out of there.

1350
01:48:54.778 --> 01:48:56.487
You're a father now. Brian.

1351
01:48:56.571 --> 01:48:58.739
No. I'm not leaving you.
Now you stick with the plan!

1352
01:48:59.449 --> 01:49:00.824
It was always the plan.

1353
01:49:01.576 --> 01:49:02.868
Take care of Mia.

1354
01:49:02.953 --> 01:49:05.371
Dom. you listen to me now. Okay?

1355
01:49:05.455 --> 01:49:07.289
You cut loose right now.

1356
01:49:23.598 --> 01:49:24.557
(SPEAKING PORTUGUESE)

1357
01:49:24.641 --> 01:49:25.683
Hey. what is he doing?

1358
01:49:29.646 --> 01:49:30.771
We've got him!

1359
01:49:47.622 --> 01:49:48.872
Close down the bridge!

1360
01:50:23.116 --> 01:50:24.491
Do something. asshole!

1361
01:50:36.588 --> 01:50:37.713
Kill him. dammit!

1362
01:50:49.100 --> 01:50:50.559
Kill him now!

1363
01:51:21.633 --> 01:51:22.633
(SCREAMING)

1364
01:51:47.701 --> 01:51:48.701
(PANTING)

1365
01:52:02.257 --> 01:52:04.967
I thought I told you to go on.

1366
01:52:06.928 --> 01:52:09.138
Yeah. I had to make a call.

1367
01:52:23.653 --> 01:52:24.653
(GROANING)

1368
01:52:26.740 --> 01:52:28.157
Help me.

1369
01:52:30.535 --> 01:52:32.536
That's for my team. you son of a bitch.

1370
01:52:36.708 --> 01:52:38.417
It's a hell of a mess.

1371
01:52:39.127 --> 01:52:40.753
Yeah. it is.

1372
01:52:42.255 --> 01:52:44.006
You know I can't let you two go.

1373
01:52:44.507 --> 01:52:46.091
I ain't made that way.

1374
01:52:48.845 --> 01:52:51.513
The way I see it. you've
earned yourselves 24 hours.

1375
01:52:52.682 --> 01:52:53.682
The money stays. though.

1376
01:52:55.018 --> 01:52:57.186
If I were you. I'd use the time.

1377
01:52:57.520 --> 01:53:00.522
Make peace with whatever
demons you got left.

1378
01:53:04.986 --> 01:53:06.862
Because come tomorrow.

1379
01:53:08.239 --> 01:53:09.364
I will find you.

1380
01:53:21.211 --> 01:53:22.503
Toretto!

1381
01:53:23.421 --> 01:53:24.713
I'll see you soon.

1382
01:53:27.550 --> 01:53:29.426
No. you won't.

1383
01:54:10.885 --> 01:54:11.969
Thanks. guys.

1384
01:54:12.053 --> 01:54:13.554
I'll see you on the other side.

1385
01:54:18.434 --> 01:54:20.894
You guys just carved
out a 10 second window.

1386
01:54:20.979 --> 01:54:22.271
Make it count!

1387
01:54:38.121 --> 01:54:39.121
(LAUGHING)

1388
01:54:53.553 --> 01:54:54.553
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

1389
01:55:04.689 --> 01:55:06.398
Come on. baby.

1390
01:55:06.482 --> 01:55:08.358
Don't be mean.

1391
01:55:10.612 --> 01:55:11.612
Come on.

1392
01:55:13.197 --> 01:55:14.197
(VAULT SCANNER BEEPING)

1393
01:55:17.160 --> 01:55:18.160
(VAULT UNLOCKING) (SIGHING)

1394
01:55:49.651 --> 01:55:50.651
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1395
01:56:23.226 --> 01:56:26.687
"For Rosa and Nico. See you soon.
- Uncle Dom"

1396
01:56:33.569 --> 01:56:37.030
MONACO

1397
01:56:38.574 --> 01:56:39.658
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

1398
01:56:39.742 --> 01:56:40.826
You sure about this?

1399
01:56:42.620 --> 01:56:44.079
You know I am.

1400
01:56:46.040 --> 01:56:47.499
You don't need to do this.

1401
01:56:48.501 --> 01:56:50.836
Just leave me alone.

1402
01:56:50.920 --> 01:56:52.963
Bro. I'm not trying to
be negative. but casinos

1403
01:56:53.172 --> 01:56:55.882
are the kinds of places designed to
take money from guys like you and me.

1404
01:56:56.050 --> 01:56:59.720
When I win here I'm buying you a
lifetime supply of antidepressants.

1405
01:57:00.013 --> 01:57:03.015
You don't put ten million on red!

1406
01:57:03.099 --> 01:57:04.057
Enough already.

1407
01:57:04.142 --> 01:57:05.517
You put it on black.

1408
01:57:07.061 --> 01:57:08.020
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1409
01:57:08.104 --> 01:57:09.229
No more bets.

1410
01:57:35.256 --> 01:57:37.466
Right this way. my dear.

1411
01:57:39.510 --> 01:57:41.344
You stay right here. I'll be right back.

1412
01:57:43.181 --> 01:57:45.348
So. this is your dream. huh?

1413
01:57:45.433 --> 01:57:46.725
It's enough for me. man.

1414
01:57:46.809 --> 01:57:48.226
I take it that's your dream.

1415
01:57:48.311 --> 01:57:50.896
Absolutely. What up.
boy? What's going on?

1416
01:57:50.980 --> 01:57:52.773
You good? Yes. yes.

1417
01:57:52.857 --> 01:57:54.066
You know what's crazy?

1418
01:57:54.150 --> 01:57:56.735
There's only four of those
cars in the whole world.

1419
01:57:57.278 --> 01:57:59.696
Yeah. I got the only one
in the Western Hemisphere.

1420
01:58:00.198 --> 01:58:04.493
I made a sheikh in Abu Dhabi
an offer he could not refuse.

1421
01:58:04.827 --> 01:58:07.079
Huh. That's a nice
lady you got there. too.

1422
01:58:07.163 --> 01:58:10.582
Absolutely. What's happening? (LAUGHING)

1423
01:58:11.375 --> 01:58:13.585
We got to go. man. Let's do this.

1424
01:58:13.669 --> 01:58:15.337
Okay. I'll drive.

1425
01:58:15.421 --> 01:58:17.964
In that? Come on. man. no way.

1426
01:58:18.049 --> 01:58:20.342
No. no. Not in this.

1427
01:58:20.426 --> 01:58:21.593
In that.

1428
01:58:27.934 --> 01:58:29.476
Are you serious right now?

1429
01:58:30.269 --> 01:58:31.603
Man. this is crazy!

1430
01:58:31.687 --> 01:58:36.274
Yes. I guess that means there are
two in the Western Hemisphere. huh?

1431
01:58:37.151 --> 01:58:39.486
What's your smart ass got to say now?

1432
01:58:40.029 --> 01:58:43.448
You know what? We can
always shine together. baby.

1433
01:58:43.533 --> 01:58:45.909
Get dressed. man. we got things to do!

1434
01:58:58.339 --> 01:58:59.798
So. where to now?

1435
01:58:59.882 --> 01:59:01.424
I don't know.

1436
01:59:01.509 --> 01:59:03.885
Never been to Madrid.

1437
01:59:03.970 --> 01:59:06.721
I thought you wanted to go to Tokyo.

1438
01:59:06.806 --> 01:59:08.974
We'll get there.

1439
01:59:09.058 --> 01:59:10.684
Eventually.

1440
02:00:10.036 --> 02:00:11.870
BRIAN: Nice surprise.

1441
02:00:15.458 --> 02:00:17.125
Crazy. right?

1442
02:00:25.343 --> 02:00:28.386
This is the happiest
I've ever seen my sister.

1443
02:00:29.430 --> 02:00:31.431
It's because we're free.

1444
02:00:44.779 --> 02:00:47.030
You know. I want another shot.

1445
02:00:50.576 --> 02:00:51.576
Yeah?

1446
02:00:53.663 --> 02:00:55.330
Yeah.

1447
02:00:55.414 --> 02:00:57.249
No wagers. nobody else.

1448
02:00:57.333 --> 02:00:59.501
Just you and me. once and for all.

1449
02:01:06.592 --> 02:01:08.551
You sure you can handle
the disappointment?

1450
02:01:09.428 --> 02:01:10.845
Are you?

1451
02:01:13.140 --> 02:01:15.225
All right. O'Conner.

1452
02:01:15.309 --> 02:01:17.143
Let's see what you got.

1453
02:03:25.689 --> 02:03:30.235
DIPLOMATIC SECURITY SERVICE HEADQUARTERS
- WASHINGTON. D.C.

1454
02:03:33.280 --> 02:03:34.280
(TYPING)

1455
02:03:45.000 --> 02:03:46.835
You need to look at that.

1456
02:03:50.756 --> 02:03:52.715
Berlin. 3:00 a.m. this morning.

1457
02:03:52.967 --> 02:03:55.760
A team of drivers
hijacked a military convoy.

1458
02:03:55.845 --> 02:03:57.679
Toretto? Nope.

1459
02:03:58.681 --> 02:03:59.639
I ain't interested.

1460
02:03:59.723 --> 02:04:02.559
Yes. you are. Keep looking.

1461
02:04:14.071 --> 02:04:15.905
Do you believe in ghosts?

1462
02:04:16.305 --> 02:05:16.563
